<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
If the numeric status code requires more than 3 digits (e.g. rcode in range 1000..9999) and the write buffer has only the minimum reserved space (buf_size == pos + 5), the code will overflow: after writing the initial ' ' the call MHD_uint16_to_str is given buf_size - pos == 4 and may successfully write 4 digits, advancing pos by 4 to pos0+5; the subsequent buf[pos++] = ' ' will attempt to write at index pos0+5 (== buf_size), which is out of bounds. In short, the code assumes a 3-digit code but does not enforce it, so with a 4-digit code and minimal buffer space an out-of-bounds access can occur.
</scenario>
